Precipitation for May 2020 shows drier than average conditions over
western and central Europe and the Balkans, with the exception of the
Iberian Peninsula. Precipitation was also generally below average,
although less consistently so across the the southwestern part of the
same regions. England also saw its driest May on record.
<br><br>
The regions surrounding the Baltic Sea generally saw below average
precipitation, while over the northeastern and eastern parts of Europe
precipitation was generally above average.
<br><br>
A small region in western France saw above average precipitation,
mainly due to a short-lived event mid-month, which led to flooding in
several locations. This can nicely be seen in the maximum 1-day
precipitation amount in May 2020 (Figure 6).
