<h3>Radiation and Cloudiness</h3>
<br><br>
The persistent high pressure over the British Isles was also responsible for an exceptionally low cloudiness and therefore for an exceptionally sunny May, especially in northwestern Europe. Corresponding with the low cloud amount, the northwestern part of Europe was also the region receiving the largest surplus of radiation with anomalies of 50 W/m&#178; and more.
The northeastern part of Europe, on the contrary, which saw an exceptionally wet May, was also the region with the largest deficit in radiation which summed up to 50 W/m&#178; and more.
